# Collaboration Protocol

This document defines the structured approach for human-AI collaboration.

---

## Session Types

| Type | Trigger | Process | Outputs |
|------|---------|---------|---------|
| Plan Review | Plan file created with all sections | Critique and expand plan; identify gaps | Updated plan, identified gaps |
| Spike Session | High uncertainty or unvalidated assumptions | Time-boxed prototype (2-4 hrs); document findings | Spike findings, decision |
| Execution Session | Plan approved and ready | Implement plan steps; check off as completed | Code, tests, updated checklist |
| Retrospective | Plan execution complete | What worked, what was harder, discoveries, follow-ups | Retrospective notes, backlog items |

### Plan Review

- **Trigger**: Plan file created with all required sections
- **Process**: Devil's advocate review, expansion review, dependency verification
- **Outputs**: Updated plan, interface contracts for exports

### Spike Session

- **Trigger**: Plan has high uncertainty; critical assumptions unvalidated
- **Process**: Time-box to 2-4 hours; prototype; document findings and decision
- **Outputs**: Spike document, decision (proceed/pivot/defer)

### Execution Session

- **Trigger**: Plan approved; dependencies ready; no blockers
- **Process**: Follow execution steps in order; run validation; update checklist
- **Outputs**: Code, tests, updated plan, runbook if user-facing

### Retrospective

- **Trigger**: Plan execution complete
- **Process**: What worked, what was harder, discoveries, actionable follow-ups
- **Outputs**: Retrospective notes, learnings to tracker, backlog items

